# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file when possible.

The format is based on Keep a Changelog:
https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/

## [Unreleased]

### Added
- Added a voxel-guided CO adsorption/desorption MCMD nanoparticle example using
  ORB-V3 CPU by default.

### Changed
- Renamed the previous Wulff nanoparticle MC example to
  ``examples/mc/orb_v3_co_mcmd.py`` and updated the quickstart around MCMD
  coverage control.

### Fixed
- None.

## [0.2.13] - 2026-07-03

### Added
- Expanded pytest coverage for NumPy voxel-grid arithmetic, plotting helpers,
  analysis edge cases, lazy imports, vector-field plotting, and Numba backend
  equivalence.

### Fixed
- Matched Numba distance-mask division behavior to NumPy for zero-distance
  center voxels in real-valued grids.

## [0.2.12] - 2026-07-03

### Changed
- Changed the voxel-guided MC example temperature to Kelvin and converted
  Metropolis sampling internally with ``kB*T``.
- Changed MC trial-site selection to prefer voxel sites local to the selected
  atom, avoiding strained global trial directions.
- Added command-line controls for the MC shell/core mask multipliers, sampled
  count range, maximum sampled sites, and local trial-site radius.
- Updated the quickstart MC image to a 1500 K EMT run with about 20%
  acceptance and final-state displacement coloring.

## [0.2.11] - 2026-07-02

### Added
- Added GitLab CI coverage reporting with pytest-cov terminal output and a
  Cobertura ``coverage.xml`` report artifact.
- Added an ASE-rendered initial/final nanoparticle state image for the
  voxel-guided MC quickstart.
- Added ``--state-plot`` to ``examples/mc/orb_v3_wulff_mc.py``.

### Changed
- Replaced the quickstart MC geometric placeholder score with ASE EMT as the
  default scorer.
- Consolidated documentation pages into a simpler navigation structure while
  keeping lightweight compatibility pages for older documentation URLs.
- Fixed the ORB-V3 quickstart scorer so the conservative model can use
  autograd during prediction.

## [0.2.10] - 2026-07-02

### Added
- Added optional Numba backends for experimental field-valued grids:
  ``FieldVoxelGridNumba`` and ``VectorVoxelGridNumba``.
- Added ASE trajectory output for the voxel-guided MC quickstart example.
- Added probe-center accessibility analysis from supplied positions, atomic
  radii, and probe radius.
- Added sampled probe-accessible surface-area estimation for inflated atom
  surfaces.
- Added a probe pore-volume documentation page with a BEA comparison against
  PoreBlazer.

### Changed
- Clarified the algorithm documentation around cached sphere stencils and
  scaling relative to all grid-point-by-atom distance scans.
- Renamed the voxel-guided MC example folder from ``examples/mcmd`` to
  ``examples/mc`` and removed MCMD wording.
- Ignored local ``tmp/`` scratch folders so compiled comparison tools and
  generated reference outputs are not tracked.

### Fixed
- Aligned the field-grid normal-mask documentation visual with voxel centers.

## [0.2.9] - 2026-07-01

### Added
- Added an experimental NumPy-only ``FieldVoxelGrid`` for scalar, vector, and
  matrix-valued voxel fields.
- Added ``VectorVoxelGrid`` as a convenience field grid for three-component
  vector fields, including atom-normal sphere masks and Matplotlib quiver
  plotting helpers.
- Added field-grid documentation, tests, and a reproducible normal-mask visual
  example.

## [0.2.8] - 2026-06-30

### Added
- Added ``dtype`` support for voxel grids, including integer, floating, and
  complex NumPy dtypes where backend support is available.
- Added a dtype benchmark script for comparing grid storage types.
- Documented dtype behavior and performance considerations.

### Changed
- Complex grids now support arithmetic sphere operations but reject ordered
  operations such as ``min_sphere``, ``clamp_grid``, range sampling, and
  threshold plotting.

## [0.2.7] - 2026-06-29

### Added
- First public release in a documentation ready state
- Taichi, CuPy, and Numba accelerators implemented
